    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Types of Radiator We Supply and Fit Across the Wirral</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Every type of radiator found in Wirral homes. We advise on the right choice for your room before any work begins.</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Standard single and double panel radiators</strong><p>The most common type across the Wirral. Double convector (type 22) panels deliver the highest heat output for their size and are our standard recommendation for most Wirral rooms. Available in all standard lengths and heights. Correctly sized for the room at the quote stage.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Column radiators for period Wirral properties</strong><p>Traditional steel column radiators in two, three and four column configurations. Available in heights from 600mm to 1800mm. Correct for high-ceilinged Victorian and Edwardian properties in CH41 to CH45 and period houses in CH47 and CH48. We calculate the required output before recommending a column specification.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Designer and vertical radiators</strong><p>Vertical designer radiators are a good solution for rooms where horizontal wall space is limited. We advise on output requirements before supply. Designer radiators with low surface area can underperform in larger Wirral rooms if not correctly specified.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Bathroom towel rails and heated towel radiators</strong><p>Chrome, white and anthracite finishes. Connected to your central heating circuit or dual fuel versions that work independently from the main system. Useful in Wirral properties where the bathroom is not always heated with the rest of the house.</p></div></div>
      </div>
